data.content:
## What Breaks in .NET 11

In .NET 10, the Cosmos DB provider let you opt in to sync-over-async execution (e.g., `EnableSyncExecution()`). **In .NET 11 (EF Core 11), that opt-in is removed entirely.** All synchronous LINQ operators and `SaveChanges()` on the Cosmos provider now throw `InvalidOperationException`.

**Every call in your repository is affected:**

| Breaks | Replacement |
|---|---|
| `.ToList()` | `.ToListAsync()` |
| `.First(...)` | `.FirstAsync(...)` |
| `.Count()` | `.CountAsync()` |
| `.SaveChanges()` | `.SaveChangesAsync()` |

### Migrated Code

```csharp
public class ProductRepository
{
    private readonly CosmosDbContext _context;

    public async Task<List<Product>> GetAllAsync()
    {
        return await _context.Products.ToListAsync();
    }

    public async Task<Product> GetByIdAsync(int id)
    {
        return await _context.Products.FirstAsync(p => p.Id == id);
    }

    public async Task<int> GetCountAsync()
    {
        return await _context.Products.CountAsync();
    }

    public async Task SaveAsync(Product product)
    {
        _context.Products.Add(product);
        await _context.SaveChangesAsync();
    }
}
```

You'll also need to propagate `async`/`await` up through all callers (controllers, services, etc.). There is no workaround — the Cosmos SDK is async-only, and EF Core no longer wraps it for you.
